          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "round": 1,
      "round_explanation": "By the start of round 1, some information has effectively leaked through the pattern of acceptances. Otter has willingly traded away BLUE for RED and then GREEN for BLUE, signaling that otter is relatively indifferent between BLUE and GREEN but values RED strongly. Peacock traded away GREEN for RED and had an early offer rejected, suggesting that peacock also rates RED highly but is not eager to move BLUE just yet. Cat successfully bought BLUE with GREEN from otter, slightly reinforcing the possibility that cat values BLUE more. With these signals, the second-round dynamics shift: otter may continue to churn low-valued BLUE into higher-valued RED, but now also has more BLUE holdings after the previous trade. Peacock, seeing that otter and cat both engaged in trades, may seek a more clearly profitable move, perhaps trying to arbitrage GREEN or BLUE. Cat, confident in a high BLUE valuation, might start to test whether others will part with additional BLUE in exchange for GREEN, or even limited amounts of RED. However, players are still cautious; no one wants to overpay in RED, so GREEN is likely to be the main payment token in this round, with BLUE being shifted to whoever privately values it most.",
